*** Rationale
The system must generate daily reports in PDF, HTML, and JSON formats.
To ensure these remain accessible for years without expiring, we upload them to S3 and generate permanent links.
This avoids the cost of maintaining a dedicated web server or expensive reporting tools while satisfying the delivery requirements.

*** Prompt
Act as a DevOps Engineer. Build a reporting and delivery system.

Task: Every 24 hours, query Click House to calculate: the highest number of DNS resolutions, total resolution counts, and resolution origins.
Formats: Generate the report in .pdf, .html, and .json.
Delivery: Email these reports to a set of users.
Persistence: Upload the reports to an S3 bucket and generate permanent links that do not expire, ensuring they remain accessible for years.
Constraint: Minimize compute usage to ensure the total pipeline stays under 800 dollars per month.
